<HEADLINE>
<P>
SCHOOL OPENINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Patricia Freeman's musings (Commentary, Sept. 2) about the annual return to 
school capture the sense of adventure and discovery that many teachers feel.The 
excitement of the start of a new school year is not the exclusive domain of 
students. That excitement is part of what has drawn me to my classroom three 
times in the past week, even though school doesn't start until today. 
</P>
<P>
 Despite all the negative political, social, and economic threats that surround 
public education today, the basic unit of education -- kids and their teacher 
-- is alive and well, and it will continue to be our society's best hope for 
the future. 
</P>
<P>
 BILL RAABE 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
