<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOT AVOCADOS? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I can't believe what I read about the avocado being best eaten raw ("Mastering 
the Avocado," Aug. 25).It's dead wrong. Traveling through Great Britain a few 
years ago, my sister and I were lucky enough to have hot avocados as a first 
course on two occasions. We scoured the menus after our first experience, 
hoping to have the dish every night. A half avocado appeared to have been baked 
and then served with the cavity filled with bay shrimp in a light 
lemon-wine-butter sauce. We both would kill for the recipe. It looked and 
tasted divine. Prior to this, I had never cared much for avocados unless they 
were in guacamole. 
</P>
<P>
 -- CLAUDIA SAWAYA 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine 
</P>
