<P>
COASTAL PANEL TO WEIGH DREDGING PLAN SEPT. 15 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An Army Corps of Engineers plan to dredge accumulated debris from the Marina 
del Rey entrance channel and dispose of it in the port will be discussed at a 
public hearing next week. 
</P>
<P>
 Originally scheduled to take place in Long Beach last month, the California 
Coastal Commission hearing was postponed so that more information could be 
gathered about the plan.The commission decided to conduct the hearing at its 
next regular meeting: Sept. 15 in Eureka. 
</P>
<P>
 A Coastal Commission staff report has recommended rejecting the plan, which 
would put the dredged waste on the port's ocean floor. 
</P>
<P>
 Commission spokesman Larry Simon recently said the waste is contaminated with 
pollutants that have drained into the channel from Ballona Creek. 
</P>
<P>
 The public hearing will be at the Eureka Inn, at 7th and F streets, at 9 a.m. 
SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
