<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MAN FACES TRIAL IN SEXUAL ASSAULT CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former nursing aide who was charged with raping a teen-age patient at a 
Ventura psychiatric hospital will be arraigned Sept. 19 in Ventura County 
Superior Court. 
</P>
<P>
 Robert Anthony Gialloreto, 21, of Oxnard was bound over for trial Tuesday on 
charges that he raped and sexually assaulted a patient at Vista del Mar 
Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Gialloreto, who pleaded not guilty Aug. 22 at his Municipal Court arraignment, 
is charged with having sexual intercourse with an incompetent person, even 
though the 18-year-old woman was a willing participant, Deputy Dist. Atty. Tom 
Connors said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the preliminary hearing, Dr. Robert Auric testified that his patient, a 
Ventura woman who voluntarily admitted herself to the hospital, was not 
competent enough to have given consent for sexual relations with the defendant, 
Connors said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gialloreto's attorney, John R. Sheehan of Burbank, could not be reached 
Wednesday for comment. 
</P>
<P>
 According to accounts given to Ventura police, a supervising nurse of the 
hospital entered a closed conference room July 20 and came upon Gialloreto and 
the patient. 
</P>
<P>
 Gialloreto, when told to leave, did so and then turned himself in to police, 
Connors said. 
</P>
<P>
 Joan Galvan, the hospital's director of marketing, said Gialloreto had worked 
at the facility "a short amount of time" and was no longer employed there. She 
refused further comment. 
</P>
<P>
 Gialloreto, who remained in custody Wednesday in lieu of $20,000 bail, was 
charged with sexually assaulting the 18-year-old July 19 and 20, Connors said. 
</P>
<P>
 The prosecutor added that Gialloreto had been in the mental health field for 
about three years and had worked at another facility before starting at the 
Ventura hospital in June. GREG RIPPEE 
</P>
