<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SoCal Drops Gas Prices for Core Customers: Southern California Gas Co. has 
reduced the price it charges for natural gas at the Southern California border 
by 7.3%, the utility said.Core customers are dependent on the SoCal system, 
have no access to alternative fuels and buy directly from the utility. The new 
rate will be $1.662 per million British thermal units, 12.26 cents per million 
BTUs less than the August price of $1.7846. Traders cited low weather-related 
demand and high levels of natural gas in storage as the main reasons for the 
low futures prices. 
</P>
</TEXT>
