<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; POLICE 
SEEK SUSPECTS IN SLAYING OF 2, WOUNDING OF 1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were fatally shot and a third man was seriously wounded in an attack 
at 47th Street and Western Avenue in Los Angeles on Wednesday afternoon, police 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said the victims, whose names and ages were not released, were shot 
between 2 p.m. and 2:15 p.m. The motive for the shootings remained unknown 
Wednesday afternoon and there were no suspects, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 LAPD Lt. Faryl Fletcher said one victim was pronounced dead at the scene, 
another was pronounced dead at Daniel Freeman Memorial Hospital and the third 
was believed to be undergoing surgery at Martin Luther King Jr. Hospital. All 
three men apparently suffered head wounds, Fletcher said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials said there may have been more than one assailant. "It does not 
appear at this time to be a drive-by," Fletcher said. 
</P>
