<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; MORE THAN A THREE-RING CIRCUS ACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hula-Hoop twirling may be long past as a national craze, but for Andrea 
Tabares it's a way of life, as she demonstrated Wednesday by spinning more than 
five of them at the same time. 
</P>
<P>
 About 90 delighted children from Jackson Elementary School gaped as the circus 
performer gyrated and spun the colored plastic hoops during a performance at 
the Discovery Museum. 
</P>
<P>
 The show was an exhibition by Circus Vargas, which is playing at the Anaheim 
Indoor Marketplace through Sunday, museum spokeswoman Linda Edwards said. 
</P>
<P>
 Tabares is one of dozens of performers who display their talents at the 
Marketplace, at Anaheim Boulevard and Cerritos Avenue, Edwards said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shows are at 4:30 and 7:30 p.m. through Friday and 12:30, 3:30 and 7:30 p.m. 
Saturday. Sunday shows are at 12:30, 3:30 and 5:30 p.m. Seats for children 
range from $4 to $14.50. For adults, prices are $8.50 to $18.50. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 535-2889. JON NALICK 
</P>
