<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: RANCHO PALOS VERDES; 
COUNCIL ACTS TO BAN NUDITY AT POPULAR BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has given preliminary approval to a citywide ban on public 
nudity because of complaints about lewd activity and transients at Smuggler's 
Cove, a popular nude sunbathing spot. 
</P>
<P>
 The council unanimously approved the ban Tuesday after listening to a parade 
of residents unhappy about the crowd being drawn to the beach, witnessing lewd 
acts and finding the beach littered with condoms. 
</P>
<P>
 Bill Ruth, who lives on a hill above the cove, said many people are afraid to 
visit the beach. 
</P>
<P>
 "This problem is not benign and it is not going away," Ruth said. "Nude and 
lewd conduct has driven out local families. It is not safe for kids." 
</P>
<P>
 City Hall received letters from nudists opposing the ban and a few people 
spoke against the idea. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am personally not a nudist," said Raymond Green. "But I know some nudists 
and they are some of the most wonderful, giving people I know." 
</P>
<P>
 If the ordinance is adopted in two weeks, the nudity ban would go into effect 
in late October. 
</P>
</TEXT>
