<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE RELEASE SKETCH OF MAN FOUND DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Orange County Sheriff's Department has released an artist's sketch of a 
man whose burned and decomposed body was found Aug. 8 in San Clemente. 
</P>
<P>
 Two residents looking for a lost animal discovered the body near a 
construction site in the area of Diamante and Calle Fino Clarete. 
</P>
<P>
 Based on bone structure and X-rays, forensic investigators said the man could 
have been Anglo, Latino or African American, 17 to 23 years old, 5 feet 5 and 
weighing 105 to 110 pounds. The man was wearing a red, white and blue striped 
flannel shirt, blue jeans and a black, woven-leather belt. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Sheriff's Lt. Dan Martini, the victim had a distinctive, crooked 
right-front tooth. Police found several handbills near his body advertising an 
income tax and document company on Bristol Street in Santa Ana. The handbills 
are modeled on a $1,000 bill. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information about the man's identity is asked to contact 
investigator Bob Blackburn at (714) 647-7048; Sgt. Randy Benicky at (714) 
647-7044; or the sheriff's watch commander at (714) 834-6490. 
</P>
