<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; GERMANY; LAST FLAG-LOWERING AT U.S. ARMY POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Stars and Stripes was lowered for the last time over U.S. Army 
headquarters in Berlin, formally ending the American presence in the 
once-divided city after nearly half a century. U.S. Maj. Gen. Walter Yates 
stood stiffly to attention as five infantrymen wearing battle dress folded up 
the banner in a solemn 10-minute ceremony at dusk under cloudy skies. The flag 
will be handed to U.S. Secretary of Defense William J. Perry this morning 
before Germany formally bids a final farewell to the Western Allies leaving 
Berlin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
