<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; NEW YORK; COURT REJECTS CORDON AT ABORTION CLINIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A federal court ruled that a buffer zone to protect a Buffalo, N.Y., abortion 
clinic from protesters was an unconstitutional restriction on free speech. In 
the ruling, the U.S. 2nd Circuit Court of Appeals said the 15-foot protective 
zone around the clinic, included in a federal court injunction against abortion 
protesters from Project Rescue, was too restrictive and thus violated the 
protesters' rights. The ruling comes two months after the U.S. Supreme Court 
approved a 36-foot sanctuary around a Melbourne, Fla., clinic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
