<HEADLINE>
<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; ILLINOIS; MEN SUE FAA, SAY THEY WERE GROPED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The FAA paid for cultural diversity training in which men had to walk past 
female co-workers who fondled them and made remarks about their sexual 
attributes, agency employees said. The training, designed to turn the tables on 
men to sensitize them to bias, went too far, said employees pursuing legal 
action in Chicago. Douglas P. Hartman, an air traffic controller who is suing 
the Transportation Department, said in June, 1992, he and others were pressured 
to walk through a line of female controllers who fondled their private parts 
and rated their sexual attributes. 
</P>
