<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; FORUM TO FOCUS ON CRIME PREVENTION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A two-hour anti-crime forum will be held by Pasadena's City Council on Tuesday 
evening in the ballroom at the Doubletree Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
 The session will feature displays of Pasadena's police cars and firetrucks, a 
video about crime prevention efforts and a round-table discussion.Issues will 
include whether the city should concentrate on youth crime prevention programs 
or increased police enforcement. Participants will include members of the Boys 
Club, the Coalition for a Non-Violent City and La Escuela de Comunidad. 
</P>
<P>
 The session's goal is to develop a stronger partnership with the community and 
obtain information from residents. The forum will run from 7:30 to 9:30 p.m. at 
the hotel, 191 N. Los Robles Ave. Free parking is available at a vacant lot at 
the southwest corner of Los Robles Avenue and Union Street. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA090894-0220 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 077089 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 8, 1994, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
San Gabriel Valley; Part J; Page 14 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
