<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: TEMPLE CITY; CHILDREN ORGANIZE FUND-RAISER FOR FRIEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 When 15-year-old Jenny Barrett's leukemia went into remission last summer, she 
joined the Temple City Tigersharks Summer Swim Team. 
</P>
<P>
 When Jenny lost her battle against the disease and died this summer, her 
teammates decided to suit up in a tribute to their friend. 
</P>
<P>
 Thirty-four children between the ages of 7 and 17 swam 1,160 laps in a 
swim-a-thon at the Temple City High School pool that raised more than $1,500 
for the Bone Marrow Treatment Center at Childrens Hospital in Los Angeles, 
where Jenny had three bone marrow transplants. 
</P>
<P>
 The swim-a-thon was organized by Jenny's friend and teammate, Erica Martin. 
Erica, 11, had initiated a prior fund-raiser for another friend, Jaiye 
Odujinrin, who died from a brain tumor in 1993. She raised $1,100 in 
Odujinrin's name and donated it to his favorite cause, the World Wildlife Fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
