BASEBALL STRIKE: DEVELOPMENTS FROM DAY 27 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Games lost: 14. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total games lost: 352. 
</P>
<P>
 * Games remaining: 317. 
</P>
<P>
 * Total income lost by players: $119.3 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Estimated revenue lost by owners: $229.5 million. 
</P>
<P>
 * Key development: Bargaining teams from both sides traveled to New York to 
prepare for a possible new proposal by the union. 
</P>
<P>
 * In quotes: "If we make a proposal, it will be because we believe we've come 
up with something new based on information we were given last weekend."  
</P>
<P>
 -- Donald Fehr union head 
</P>
