<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: SAILORS' PENCE TO ATTEND UCSB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DON TURNBULL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Brad Pence, an All-American and second-team Times all-county water polo player 
from Newport Harbor High, will attend UC Santa Barbara this fall, he said 
Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 A two-year starter, Pence was the team MVP last season with 87 goals for the 
Sailors -- who finished second (17-9) in the Sea View League and made the 
Southern Section Division I playoffs -- and totaled more than 100 goals in his 
high school career. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Fred Leininger has stepped down as Cypress High boys' soccer coach. He had 
coached as a walk-on at the school since 1980, taking over the varsity in 1986. 
</P>
<P>
 His teams were 70-39-28 in nine years, reaching the section quarterfinals last 
season and the semifinals in 1990. 
</P>
<P>
 Leininger quit to accept a full-time teaching job at a local continuation 
school. He will remain as an assistant men's soccer coach at Cypress College. 
DON TURNBULL 
</P>
</TEXT>
