</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TURN Proposes Electric Deregulation Plan: Toward Utility Rate Normalization, 
the San Francisco-based consumer advocate group, described an alternative to 
the California Public Utilities Commission plan to deregulate the state's 
investor-owned electric utilities.Under the TURN proposal, local governmental 
agencies -- cities, counties, water districts and similar bodies -- would 
establish "consumer-owned utilities." These would be much like existing 
municipal utilities but without generating plants or a distribution system. 
These local utilities would shop for electricity on the wholesale generating 
market, pay for distribution on existing utility lines and sell the power to 
consumers, from residential to big industrial users. The PUC plan calls for a 
direct retail market for consumers. 
</P>
