<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAXWELL HOUSE RAISES COFFEE PRICES AGAIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Coffee prices are rising again. 
</P>
<P>
 Maxwell House Coffee Co. said Wednesday that it is boosting the price of its 
ground coffee by 6.8% and its instant coffee by 5.7% in response to recent 
increases in the cost of raw beans. 
</P>
<P>
 Maxwell House now charges the same for a 13-ounce can of its flagship ground 
coffee -- $3.16 wholesale -- as Procter & Gamble charges for its Folgers ground 
coffee. 
</P>
<P>
 Folgers, the best-selling coffee brand in the United States last year, posted 
an identical 20-cent-a-can hike Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Maxwell House has changed prices six times in less than 2 1/2 months, raising 
them four times and lowering them twice as it responded to changes in the price 
of unprocessed coffee beans. 
</P>
<P>
 World coffee markets have been rocked because cold and dry weather has damaged 
the crop in Brazil, cutting the potential supply from the world's biggest 
producer. 
</P>
</TEXT>
