<TEXT>
<P>
 Procter & Gamble Sues Over Packaging: The company said it filed the lawsuit in 
U.S. District Court in Toledo to stop a Michigan company from selling 
private-label products in packages that resemble Procter & Gamble products.The 
suit alleges that products sold by F&M Distributors Inc. of Warren, Mich., at 
its 120 drugstores infringe on package designs of five Procter & Gamble brands. 
The packages look like Procter & Gamble's Pantene Pro-V and Head & Shoulders 
shampoos, Secret and Sure antiperspirants, and Noxzema cleansing cream, 
according to the suit. A call to F&M President Dale Ward was not immediately 
returned. 
