ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: BRIDGFORD FOODS' QUARTERLY PROFIT INCREASES BY 15% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bridgford Foods Corp., an Anaheim producer of convenience food products, 
reported profit of $1.5 million, or 15 cents a share, for its third fiscal 
quarter.That was up 15% from earnings of $1.3 million, or 14 cents a share, for 
the same period a year earlier. Sales for the quarter ended July 29 rose 3% to 
$25.6 million from $24.8 million. For the first three quarters of its fiscal 
year, the company said its profit increased 10% to $4.3 million, or 46 cents a 
share, from $3.9 million, or 41 cents a share, for the same period a year 
earlier. Nine-month sales increased 4% to $80.5 million from $77.6 million. 
