<HEADLINE>
<P>
BY DESIGN; DYEING TO HELP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KATHY ST. IVES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Finding the best dye job in town is not easy. But a few cleaners and dye 
factories are willing to do the deed. 
</P>
<P>
 Most of the people we spoke to were reluctant to quote prices over the phone. 
They said they prefer to see and feel the garment to be dyed, so they know what 
they are getting into. Prices are determined by fabric and thread count, and 
can vary widely. For example, dyeing a jacket can cost anywhere from $15 to 
$80; slacks are $15 to $50; an ordinary dress starts at about $22 and goes up 
to $60, and a vest will run you $12 to $25. 
</P>
<P>
 If the garment is not made of natural fibers, you may be asked to sign a 
waiver releasing the dyer of all responsibility -- including shrinkage. It gets 
worse: Most places will not guarantee results. 
</P>
<P>
 * A Dyeing Art, 1755 B Gardena Ave., Glendale; (818) 246-5440. 
</P>
<P>
 * Brownie's Suede and Leather Cleaners, 5422 Oceanus Drive, Huntington Beach; 
(714) 893-0085. 
</P>
<P>
 * Studio Cleaners, 10800 Washington Blvd., Culver City; (310) 838-1801. 
</P>
<P>
 * La Cienega Cleaners, 900 N. La Cienega Blvd., West Hollywood; (310) 
659-7474. 
</P>
<P>
 * Milt & Michael Master Dry Cleaners, 4021 W. Alameda Ave., Burbank; (818) 
856-4734. KATHY ST. IVES 
</P>
</TEXT>
