<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; THE ARTS: MUSIC CENTER SEEKS YOUNG PERFORMERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Los Angeles Music Center is hosting a talent search for high school 
students involved in the performing arts.  
</P>
<P>
 The seventh annual "The Music Center Spotlight Awards," sponsored by the 
Telesis Foundation, is open to Southern California high school students 
involved in ballet, jazz or modern dance, opera, musical theater or pop vocal, 
classical and jazz instrumental music. 
</P>
<P>
 Event organizers expect more than 600 students to audition in October and 
November for the Spotlight awards. Only 15 students will be selected for the 
semifinals. The students will train in master classes with members of the Los 
Angeles Philharmonic, the Los Angeles Music Center Opera and other 
professionals. 
</P>
<P>
 The final competition will be narrowed to a field of 12, two competitors in 
each category, performing in front of a live audience at the Dorothy Chandler 
Pavilion on March 22. 
</P>
<P>
 Winners will receive a $5,000 award and the runners-up will receive $2,500 to 
continue their education in the performing arts. The application deadline is 
Oct. 7. 
</P>
<P>
 For information call (213) 972-0769. 
</P>
</TEXT>
