<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; MARKETING: COMPANY; EXPANDS SERVICES IN RUSSIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Santa Monica-based marketing firm is expanding its business ventures in 
Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 Going beyond the event-promotion it already conducts in Russia, Comspan 
Entertainment Marketing -- formerly Comspan Inc. -- plans to undertake consumer 
research, media buying and other services for companies interested in doing 
business in Russia. 
</P>
<P>
 It is doing so in partnership with a Russian company -- White Nights Assn. of 
St. Petersburg. 
</P>
<P>
 Comspan will continue to organize, market and seek sponsors for events such as 
concerts, film festivals and sporting contests in Russia. The company already 
helps organize two annual events there -- "Champions Tennis Russia," a tennis 
tournament for players over 35 years old, and the White Knights International 
Cultural Festival, a music event. 
</P>
<P>
 Larry Namer, founder of Comspan and formerly of E! Entertainment TV, began 
looking into the possibility of Russian business ventures in 1989, soon 
concluding that there was ample opportunity. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a country where you can wake up in the morning and say, 'Today I want 
to start a phone company,' and literally you can," Namer said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
