<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: BEVERLY HILLS; ARNHYM TAKES CHAMBER POST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Beverly Hills Chamber of Commerce has a new executive vice president -- 
former Palm Springs Chamber of Commerce chief executive officer Rolf G. Arnhym. 
</P>
<P>
 Arnhym, 64, was scheduled to begin the $70,000-a-year job this week. He 
replaces Bill Boyd, who left the 1,130-member Beverly Hills chamber in July to 
take a job as executive director of Mediascope in Studio City. 
</P>
</TEXT>
