<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: CERRITOS; MORATORIUM PLACED ON ADULT BUSINESS PERMITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has declared a 45-day moratorium on permits for pornographic 
bookstores, X-rated movie theaters and clubs featuring nude dancing. 
</P>
<P>
 The ordinance, which took effect immediately after a unanimous vote last week, 
will stall applications until Oct. 15 for adult-oriented businesses. 
</P>
<P>
 Assistant City Manager Dennis T. Davis said the council adopted the moratorium 
because officials have received about five inquiries into adult business 
permits in the last month, and the city has no zoning laws regulating such 
businesses. The moratorium will give city staff members time to determine 
appropriate sites for the establishments. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Paul W. Bowlen and Councilman Sherman R. Kappe indicated that they will 
vote to lengthen the moratorium. "The longer it is that we can extend this, the 
longer we can delay looking at applications," Kappe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The council can extend the moratorium up to 10 1/2 months to research the 
matter. The city has not received any adult business applications in recent 
years, Davis said. "Word gets around that those types of businesses are not 
welcome here," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 City staff will not recommend that the businesses be clustered into one part 
of town, which could create an undesirable adult entertainment district, Davis 
said. JOHN CANALIS 
</P>
</TEXT>
