<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: SOUTH GATE; THEFT OF OLD GLORY RAISES A RED FLAG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SIMON ROMERO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Treason has been on the mind of City Clerk Nina Banuelos since the city's 
treasured American flag was stolen from City Council chambers last month. 
</P>
<P>
 "What kind of a person would steal a flag?" she asked. 
</P>
<P>
 According to Banuelos, the 6-by-4-foot Stars and Stripes and its 10-foot pole 
were stolen from behind the mayor's chair between Aug. 9 and 11. 
</P>
<P>
 "This could be considered treason, depending on who took it and what they did 
with it," said an irate Banuelos, 24, who was elected clerk two years ago. 
</P>
<P>
 The flagpole's stand, valued at $35, was also taken, according to the police 
report. The flag, which has been in the city's possession for more than 20 
years, was valued at $250. The pole was valued at $15. The state flag, which 
stood alongside Old Glory, was left untouched. 
</P>
<P>
 The city clerk's office has established a voice mail hot line: (213) 563-9596. 
SIMON ROMERO 
</P>
</TEXT>
