<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: COMPTON; TUCKER SEEKS DONATIONS TO LEGAL DEFENSE FUND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rep. Walter R. Tucker III (D-Compton) is asking the public to help pay for his 
legal fight against federal allegations of extortion and tax evasion. 
</P>
<P>
 "It is my obligation to myself, to my family and to my constituents to defend 
myself against these false charges," Tucker said."To do so, I would not be at 
all surprised if my legal bills approach $250,000."  
</P>
<P>
 Tucker got approval from the U.S. House Ethics Committee to create the Walter 
Tucker III Legal Defense Fund, which is headed by longtime Tucker family friend 
Mattie Taylor. Tucker, 37, pleaded not guilty Aug. 22 to 10 counts of tax 
evasion and extortion while mayor of Compton. The trial is scheduled for 
February. 
</P>
<P>
 Prosecutors allege that Tucker received $30,000 in bribes from a company that 
wanted to build a waste-to-energy plant, and he later demanded another 
$250,000. 
</P>
</TEXT>
