 BELL-JEFF GUARDS 03,14,08,10 1993 OVERALL LEAGUE PLACE 2-7-2 2-2-1 tied 3rd 
03,15,06,18 COACH YR. RECORD AT SCHOOL Doug Woodlief 10th 30-58-2 
04,31,05,05,05 TOP RETURNEES OFF DEF YR Mike Reyes, 6-4, 240 TE DE Sr. John 
Pawlik, 5-11, 195 RB SS Sr. David Quintero, 5-10, 210 FB LB Sr. Richard 
Szeptycki, 6-2, 205 QB -- Sr. David Matekel, 6-3, 195 WR FS Sr. James Jackson, 
5-10, 175 RB CB Sr. Jerome Aguilar, 5-9, 205 G -- Sr. Charlie Alarcon, 5-10, 
220 -- DL Sr. Earl Nino, 5-8, 185 G -- Sr. Jason Plourde, 5-11, 185 -- LB Sr. 
Hector Ramirez, 5-10, 180 -- LB Sr. 04,34,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR 
Ryan Ortiz, 6-3, 250 OL -- Jr. Darrill Kendig, 6-3, 235 OL -- Jr. Victor 
Castellanos, 5-6 1/2, 240 -- DL Jr. Chris Tincher, 5-10, 270 OL DL So. Tommy 
Gales, 6-3, 175 WR DB So. FAST FACT 
</P>
<P>
 Woodlief played linebacker for a 9-0-1 Memphis State team in 1963 that was 
denied a bowl bid. He went on to play for the Rams from 1965-69. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Guards have the potential to flatten opponents on the line of scrimmage 
with eight linemen weighing 200 pounds or more. But only two of those players 
have varsity experience. Quarterback Szeptycki, who passed for an average of 
only 65 yards per game last year, might be more active with Matekel emerging as 
a good receiver. Jackson and Pawlik combined for more than 1,400 rushing yards 
last year. ST. GENEVIEVE VALIANTS 03,14,08,07 1993 OVERALL LEAGUE PLACE 9-3 5-0 
1st 03,16,05,18 COACH YR. RECORD AT SCHOOL Jeff Trovatten 1st 0-0 
04,27,05,05,05 TOP RETURNEES OFF DEF YR Joe Muller, 6-1, 175 WR DB Sr. Randy 
Iaccino, 6-1, 175 QB DB Sr. Ray Cruz, 5-7, 165 RB LB Sr. Mike Hanson, 6-2, 185 
T -- Sr. Tony Orsini, 6-3, 192 T DE Sr. Vinnie Tannous, 5-10, 221 FB LB Sr. 
Kurt Vangelesti, 6-3, 185 G -- Sr. Rickey Estrada, 5-7, 176 RB LB Jr. 
04,29,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR Jorge Espinoza, 6-1, 205 -- DT Sr. Alex 
Hernandez, 6-0, 280 T -- Sr. Jesse Johnson, 5-10, 195 -- DE Sr. Eric Tapia, 
6-0, 165 TE DB Sr. Cesar Garcia, 5-10, 158 QB -- Jr. Rodney Villanueva, 6-2, 
170 QB -- Jr. Eric Morehead, 6-1, 200 OG -- Jr. James Collis, 6-0, 195 C -- Jr. 
FAST FACT 
</P>
<P>
 Trovatten has coached in big-time programs at Hart, Crespi and Saugus. This is 
his first head coaching job. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Valiants had four consecutive last-place finishes before their dramatic 
1993 turnaround. Seven starters return from that team, five of them playing 
both ways. They should contend for the 1994 title, but it won't be an easy 
road. With former Coach Richard Fong leaving the program last spring and 
Trovatten not arriving until June 20, many players showed up for two-a-day 
workouts out of shape. 
</P>
