</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick is a Los Angeles County-funded school for male juvenile offenders 
and has never had the benefit of a returning player. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Bell is optimistic about his new group of Mustangs, although many of them 
never have played football before. L.A. BAPTIST KNIGHTS 03,14,08,07 1993 
OVERALL LEAGUE PLACE 13-0 3-0 1st 03,12,05,18 COACH YR. RECORD AT SCHOOL Mark 
Bates 6th 34-22 04,29,05,05,05 TOP RETURNEES OFF DEF YR Dave Clark, 6-3, 257 OL 
DL Jr. Adrian Kaali-Nagy, 5-9, 160 WR DB Sr. Tony Marek, 6-2, 203 TE LB Sr. 
Robin Woo, 6-1, 180 QB -- Jr. Joe Romero, 5-11, 185 WR DB Sr. 04,24,05,05,05 
TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR Nathan Wendt, 6-2, 205 RB LB Sr. Jon Devirian, 6-0, 
190 TE LB Sr. FAST FACT 
</P>
<P>
 L.A. Baptist was 21-22 in five years prior to last season's Division X 
championship campaign. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Kaali-Nagy will be the featured receiver in a run-and-shoot offense. Woo 
completed just one of five passes in mop-up duty last season. VILLAGE CHRISTIAN 
