 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 There are unusual sights in the Saints' camp--the hulking bodies of Isner and 
Escudero, a spirited battle at quarterback between Super and Davis, and the 
athletically gifted Maciel. But Saints are plagued by the traditional problems: 
a roster of only 34 and too many players going both ways. Size and talent are 
better than usual. But experience, depth and attitude are concerns. "We've got 
to teach these kids how to win," Dolby said. SANTA PAULA CARDINALS 03,14,08,07 
1993 OVERALL LEAGUE PLACE 1-9 0-4 5th 03,14,05,18 COACH YR. RECORD AT SCHOOL 
Paul Spinner 2nd 1-9 04,29,05,05,05 TOP RETURNEES OFF DEF YR Austin Macias, 
