</P>
<P>
 Spinner is the only coach in the league who has not set a league championship 
as his team's goal. And with no foreseeable running attack and a quarterback 
who played part time on a 2-8 JV team last year, he's probably taking the right 
approach. The goal is reaching .500, which still seems lofty considering three 
or four linemen will play both ways and the only depth on the team is at 
receiver and defensive back. Said Spinner, "My goal is for a kid to have a fun 
experience and a positive outlet that he can channel his energies into." 
</P>
