 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Johnson's goal since taking over the Dons' program two years ago is to improve 
every season. The Dons have done that--but ever so slowly. "When you rebuild a 
program, it doesn't happen overnight," Johnson said. Unlike seasons past 
however, the Dons will have some beefy lineman to help foster more offense. And 
with seven skill-position players returning, the Dons should improve on last 
season's eight-point-per-game average and fight for a playoff spot in the newly 
formatted playoff scheme. 
</P>
