<P>
 Carr's father, George, played five years as a wide receiver and defensive back 
with Calgary of the Canadian Football League. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 The Bulldogs return 33 lettermen from a team that didn't win a game on the 
field last season (Antelope Valley forfeited it's victory over Highland for 
using an ineligible player). Parker has made several changes for 1994, 
especially the offensive attack, which switches from the I-formation to a 
one-back passing attack. Two talented transfers should make an immediate 
impact. Marcy (Fresno Edison) will start at running back and Hollingsworth 
(Rancho Buena Vista in San Diego) will lead the defense. LITTLEROCK LOBOS 
03,14,08,07 1993 OVERALL LEAGUE PLACE 4-6 2-3 4th 03,11,05,18 COACH YR. RECORD 
AT SCHOOL Jim Bauer 4th 17-13 04,29,05,05,05 TOP RETURNEES OFF DEF YR Dante 
Hinton, 6-2, 250 OL DL Sr. Eugene Dawson, 6-2, 270 OL DL Sr. Mike Kieffer, 6-3, 
220 OL DL Sr. Lawrence Larry, 6-3, 235 OL LB Sr. Mike Stewart, 5-8, 185 -- LB 
Sr. Devin Benjamin, 5-10, 180 FB LB Sr. Ceasar Flores, 5-10, 185 RB SS Sr. Andy 
Drossel, 6-3, 200 WR DB Sr. Lafayette Bailey, 5-10, 170 RB DB Jr. 
04,28,05,05,05 TOP NEWCOMERS OFF DEF YR Ceasar Flores, 5-10, 185 RB SS Sr. 
Robbie Spradlin, 5-10, 180 RB LB Jr. Jaquay Bangs, 6-2, 185 WR DB Jr. Bruce 
Johnson 6-1, 170 QB DB Jr. FAST FACT 
</P>
<P>
 The Lobos return nine starters on defense from 1993, including the entire 
line. 
</P>
<P>
 OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Experienced lines and the explosive Bailey are strengths for the Lobos. Bailey 
returned a kickoff 95 yards for a touchdown against Quartz Hill last season and 
gained 93 yards in 20 carries in limited action at running back. For additional 
help, Bauer has turned to other sports. Drossel was Golden League high hurdles 
champion and Spradlin won a league title in wrestling. "We've got enough talent 
where we can think about getting back to the playoffs," Bauer said. PALMDALE 
